cs.LO, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DM 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with proof nets of Multiplicative Linear Logic (MLL) and proposes a novel approach for analysing them. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper uses coding theory to define families of proof structures and introduce a metric space for each family. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper presents two proof-net enumeration algorithms for a given PS-family. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the efficiency of the two proof-net enumeration algorithms. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with combinatorial structures and their properties.
